Interface BillRepository

All Superinterfaces:
org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<BillEntity,Long>, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<BillEntity,Long>, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaSpecificationExecutor<BillEntity>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListCrudRepository<BillEntity,Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListPagingAndSortingRepository<BillEntity,Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.PagingAndSortingRepository<BillEntity,Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.query.QueryByExampleExecutor<BillEntity>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<BillEntity,Long>
@Repository public interface BillRepository extends org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<BillEntity,Long>, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaSpecificationExecutor<BillEntity>
Repository interface for managing bill entities.

This interface provides CRUD operations and custom query methods for interacting with the underlying database for bill entities.

    • groupByCategoryAndBillTypeBetweenPeriod

      @Query("SELECT sum(b.amount) as amount, b.categoryBill as category, b.billType as billType, count(b.expenditureId) as quantity from bill b WHERE b.period = :period AND b.billType = :billType and b.status != :status GROUP BY b.categoryBill, b.billType") List<jakarta.persistence.Tuple> groupByCategoryAndBillTypeBetweenPeriod(@Param("period") PeriodEntity period, BillTypeEntity billType, @Param("status") BillStatus status)
      Groups bills by category and bill type for a specified period.
      Parameters:
      period - The period entity used to filter the bills.
      billType - The bill type entity used to filter the bills.
      status - the status of bill, ACTIVE or CANCELLED
      Returns:
      A list of objects where each object array contains the total amount, category bill, and bill type.

    • getBillReportByPeriod

      @Query("SELECT c.categoryBillId AS categoryBillId, c.name AS categoryName, COALESCE(SUM(b.amount), 0) AS amount, COALESCE(AVG(b.amount), 0) AS average, COALESCE(COUNT(b.expenditureId), 0) AS quantity, COALESCE(MIN(b.amount), 0) AS minAmount, COALESCE(MAX(b.amount), 0) AS maxAmount, COALESCE((SUM(b.amount) * 100.0 / (SELECT SUM(sub.amount) FROM bill sub WHERE sub.period.id = :periodId AND sub.status != \'CANCELLED\')), 0) AS percentage, b.period.periodId FROM category_bill c LEFT JOIN bill b ON b.categoryBill.categoryBillId = c.categoryBillId WHERE b.period.id = :periodId AND b.status != \'CANCELLED\' AND b.billType = :billType GROUP BY c.categoryBillId ORDER BY c.name DESC") List<jakarta.persistence.Tuple> getBillReportByPeriod(@Param("periodId") Long periodId, BillTypeEntity billType)
      Retrieves a summarized report for bills within a specific period, grouped by category and bill type.
      Parameters:
      periodId - The ID of the period to filter the bills by.
      billType - The bill type to filter the bills by.
      Returns:
      A list of tuples.

    • getBillReportByPeriods

      @Query("SELECT c.categoryBillId AS categoryBillId, c.name AS categoryName, COALESCE(SUM(b.amount), 0) AS amount, COALESCE(AVG(b.amount), 0) AS average, COALESCE(COUNT(b.expenditureId), 0) AS quantity, COALESCE(MIN(b.amount), 0) AS minAmount, COALESCE(MAX(b.amount), 0) AS maxAmount, COALESCE((SUM(b.amount) * 100.0 / (SELECT SUM(sub.amount) FROM bill sub WHERE sub.period.id IN (:periodIds) AND sub.status != \'CANCELLED\')), 0) AS percentage, b.period.periodId FROM category_bill c LEFT JOIN bill b ON b.categoryBill.categoryBillId = c.categoryBillId WHERE b.period.id IN (:periodIds) AND b.status != \'CANCELLED\' AND b.billType = :billType GROUP BY c.categoryBillId, b.period.periodId ORDER BY c.name DESC") List<jakarta.persistence.Tuple> getBillReportByPeriods(List<Long> periodIds, BillTypeEntity billType)
      Retrieves a summarized report for bills across multiple periods, grouped by category and bill type.
      Parameters:
      periodIds - A list of period IDs to filter the bills by.
      billType - The bill type to filter the bills by.
      Returns:
      A list of tuples.

    • findTopSupplierIdByPeriodsAndBillType

      @Query("SELECT provv.supplierId, SUM(provv.amount) as totalAmount, SUM(provv.amount) * 100.0 / (SELECT SUM(p.amount) FROM bill p WHERE p.period.periodId IN :periodIds AND p.status != \'CANCELLED\' AND p.billType = :billType) as percentage, AVG(provv.amount) as averageAmount, MAX(provv.amount) as maxBill, MIN(provv.amount) as minBill, COUNT(provv.amount) as billCount FROM bill provv WHERE provv.period.periodId IN :periodIds AND provv.status != \'CANCELLED\' AND provv.billType = :billType GROUP BY provv.supplierId ORDER BY SUM(provv.amount) DESC") List<jakarta.persistence.Tuple> findTopSupplierIdByPeriodsAndBillType(@Param("periodIds") List<Long> periodIds, @Param("billType") BillTypeEntity billType)
      Retrieves a list of suppliers with the total amount of expenses grouped and ordered by descending amount, based on the specified periods and bill type.
      Parameters:
      periodIds - List of period IDs to filter the expenses.
      billType - Bill type to filter the results.
      Returns:
      List of `Tuple` containing supplier ID and total amount, ordered by amount in descending order.
